# Gen AI development

- Treat LLM integration as a service layer with clear input/output contracts.
- Version prompts, models, and retrieval indexes together in deployments.
- Implement eval harnesses before changing prompts or models in production.
- Stream responses for UX; buffer only when downstream processing requires full text.
- Handle provider outages with retries, fallbacks, and user-visible error states.
- Track cost per request: input tokens, output tokens, embedding calls, retrieval queries.
- Sanitize user input before prompt injection — never concatenate raw user text into system prompts blindly.
- Use tool/function calling with strict schemas instead of parsing LLM prose for actions.
- Separate dev/staging/prod API keys and rate limits.
- Comply with data retention policies — do not send PII to external LLM APIs without review.
